<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:77.30px" class="cls_003"><span class="cls_003">Sales Enablement: What is Sales Onboarding?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:120.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Hiring salespeople can be a daunting task. Organizations are always looking for talented sales</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:134.90px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">representatives with relevant industry experience and a proven track record. These are the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:149.42px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">salespeople who can sell more effectively. Even though hiring the right people is vital, every</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:163.94px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">organization runs differently and every salesperson comes with strengths and weaknesses that</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:178.46px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">are unique to them. Therefore, a different learning curve exists for each new salesperson. This</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:192.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">is where the importance of sales onboarding comes into the picture. Sales enablement teams</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:207.62px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">can drive sales onboarding by assessing, building, managing and measuring it to ensure new</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:222.14px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">salespersons have the necessary knowledge and skills.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:254.81px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">The Importance of Sales Onboarding</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:293.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Effective sales onboarding is necessary for growing sales and revenue. Not only this but:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:322.61px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Poor or incomplete sales onboarding can result in missed sales opportunities. A </span><A HREF="https://resources.careerbuilder.com/small-business/more-companies-need-structured-onboarding">study</A> </span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:337.13px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">reveals that incomplete sales onboarding can cost businesses $50,000 to $200,000</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:351.65px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">every month. Employee-oriented sales onboarding plans can mend these gaps and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:366.29px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">increase the productivity of sales representatives.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:380.81px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Thorough sales onboarding can boost customer conversion. Research shows that well-</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:395.33px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">planned sales onboarding can increase customer conversion by up to 15%.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:442.51px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">The Role of Sales Enablement Teams in Sales Onboarding</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:481.27px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Salespersons are super busy. Honestly, they don’t have additional time on their plates to focus</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:495.79px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">on tasks other than selling. So, when new sales representatives are hired, sales team leads and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:510.31px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">managers don’t have the required time and resources to provide a stellar onboarding</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:524.83px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">experience. This is where the role of sales enablement teams becomes crucial.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:553.99px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Similar to how sales enablement teams help sales teams in an organization by providing them</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:568.51px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">with the right content as and when required, it’s also necessary for them to provide new sales</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:583.06px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">employees with the resources and tools they need to get onboarded quickly.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:612.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Sales enablement teams can build a sales onboarding plan focusing on:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:641.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Knowledge</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:655.78px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Processes</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:670.42px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Skills</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:802px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.42px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">Advantages of Optimizing Your Sales Onboarding Plan</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:110.06px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Per Bridge Group, a new salesperson requires four months to get onboarded completely.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:124.70px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Businesses are struggling to bring down the onboarding time and enhance the productivity of</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:139.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">salespersons. However, this is a misconception that sales onboarding should not take more</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:153.74px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">than a couple of weeks.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:182.78px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Successful sales onboarding programs don’t end in a matter of weeks. </span><A HREF="https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C1GCEA_enIN851IN851&sxsrf=ALeKk02xoIO1oEKzX78vAcVjbSzCIsypCg:1584865156546&q=Research+suggests+that+new+sales+person+get+overwhelmed+with+the+onboarding+resources+in+the+first+30+days.&spell=1&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjhurDl0q3oAhXjnFwKHWQXAroQBSgAegQIDRAn&biw=1163&bih=510">Research</A> </span><span class="cls_002">suggests that</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:197.42px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">new salespersons get overwhelmed with the onboarding resources in the first 30 days. In the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:211.94px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">absence of ongoing reinforcement, they end up forgetting 80% of the </span><span class="cls_006">training</span><span class="cls_002">. Therefore,</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:226.46px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">businesses with excellent sales and growth have a structured sales onboarding program with</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:241.01px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">regular reinforcement.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:270.17px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">With an organized sales onboarding plan, organizations can reduce salesperson onboarding</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:284.69px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">time by almost 50%. Other benefits of a well-structured sales onboarding plan include:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:313.73px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Top sales employee retention: According to Equifax Workforce Solutions, successful</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:328.37px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">sales onboarding programs keep best-performing salespersons engaged during the first</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:342.89px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">30 days of sales onboarding.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:357.41px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Reduced sales employee turnover: </span><A HREF="https://learn.g2.com/onboarding-statistics">Research</A> </span><span class="cls_002"> shows that more than 65% of employees</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:371.93px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">can stay with an organization for at least three years if provided with proper sales</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:386.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">onboarding.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:401.09px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Satisfied managers: Effective sales onboarding training helps sales employees achieve</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:415.63px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">their targets better and quicker. The result - happy managers.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:430.15px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Improved employee engagement: Proper sales onboarding is the secret to increased</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:444.67px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">employee engagement.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:473.83px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Many organizations undermine the effectiveness of sales onboarding and focus on ad hoc</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:488.35px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">onboarding. However, that’s not the right approach. Teams with well-structured sales</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:502.87px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">onboarding programs produce more than 35% better results.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:535.51px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">What Does a Well-Structured Sales Onboarding Plan Look Like?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:574.27px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">A thorough sales onboarding plan comprises a dual-training plan:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:603.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Two to four weeks of bootcamp</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:617.86px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Three to nine months of regular reinforcement</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:665.14px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">Essential Components of a Well-Structured Sales Onboarding Plan</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:1604px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">The sales enablement team should ensure they include the following components/topics in the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:85.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">sales onboarding plan for new hires:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:114.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Company details: Include the company’s mission, value proposition, vision and so on.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:129.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Target customer profile: Share details about the company’s suitable prospects.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:144.02px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Product/service features and benefits: Train them on how to position each</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:158.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">product/service.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:173.18px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Key messaging: Once the sales representatives understand the company’s mission</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:187.70px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">statement, it’s important to tell them how to deliver the same to the customers.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:202.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Case studies/success stories: Sales representatives should have quick access to case</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:216.74px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">studies and success stories to share the experiences of existing customers with</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:231.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">prospective customers.</span></div>
</div>

